---
id: org.dxos.plugin.sequencer
name: SequencerPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A music sequencer / step-grid editor for `DXOS` Composer. A `Score` owns a set of
tracks and per-track `Sequence` objects whose `Note`s are edited on a 2D grid
(pitch on the y-axis, time on the x-axis). Backed by the canvas-based
`react-ui-canvas` `CellGrid` component.

## Notes (Phase 2)

- Edit sequences
- Arrange sequences
- Sound engine

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |

## Types

```mdl
type Note
  desc: |
    A single note in a sequence. Time fields are in beats relative to the start
    of the sequence; sub-beat values are valid (e.g. 0.25 = 16th note at 4/4).
  fields:
    pitch: int               # MIDI pitch number (0..127); 60 = middle C
    startTime: number        # in beats from start of the sequence
    duration: number         # in beats
    velocity?: number        # 0.0..1.0; defaults to 0.8
    data?: object            # opaque per-note metadata (added by patches, plugins, etc.)
```

```mdl
type Track
  desc: |
    Track metadata. A track owns its instrument/patch assignment and visual
    identity; sequences reference the track they belong to.
  fields:
    id: string
    name: string
    color?: string           # hex string for UI tinting
    instrument?: string      # opaque patch identifier (e.g. 'sf2:piano')
    minPitch?: int           # default scroll range floor; defaults to 36 (C2)
    maxPitch?: int           # default scroll range ceiling; defaults to 84 (C6)
    muted?: boolean
```

```mdl
type Sequence
  desc: |
    An ordered collection of notes associated with a single track. The sequence
    has a fixed length (in beats); notes outside that range are clipped.
  fields:
    trackId: string          # Track.id this sequence belongs to
    name?: string
    length: number           # length in beats
    notes: Note[]
```

```mdl
type Score
  desc: |
    Top-level container. Owns the track roster and a collection of sequences,
    plus playback metadata.
  fields:
    name?: string
    tempo: number            # BPM; defaults to 120
    timeSignature?: string   # e.g. '4/4'
    tracks: Track[]
    sequences: Sequence[]
```

## Components

```mdl
component SequenceGrid
  desc: |
    2D grid editor for a single Sequence. Y-axis = pitch (high pitches on top,
    matching standard piano-roll convention); x-axis = time in beats.
    Renders via @dxos/react-ui-canvas CellGrid.
  props:
    sequence: Sequence
    track: Track
    minPitch?: int           # visible pitch floor; defaults to Track.minPitch
    maxPitch?: int           # visible pitch ceiling; defaults to Track.maxPitch
    beatsPerCell?: number    # x-axis resolution; defaults to 0.25 (16th notes)
    playhead?: number        # current play position in beats, or null
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
  actions:
    addNote(note: Note)
    # Notes are identified by their (pitch, startTime) coordinates — `Note` has
    # no stable id field, matching the toggle-grid model.
    removeNote(pitch: int, startTime: number)
    updateNote(pitch: int, startTime: number, patch: Partial<Note>)
  emits:
    onNoteToggle(pitch: int, beat: number, mode: 'set' | 'unset' | 'toggle')
    onNoteResize(pitch: int, startTime: number, duration: number)
  layout: |
    ┌────────┬─────────────────────┐
    │        │ time ruler (beats)  │
    ├────────┼─────────────────────┤
    │ pitch  │                     │
    │ labels │                     │
    │ (C5)   │   note cells        │
    │ (B4)   │                     │
    │ ...    │                     │
    └────────┴─────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component TrackList
  desc: |
    Vertical list of tracks in a Score with mute/instrument controls and
    selection state. Selecting a track in the list focuses its sequence(s)
    in the SequenceGrid pane.
  props:
    score: Score
    selectedTrackId?: string
  emits:
    onSelectTrack(trackId: string)
    onMuteTrack(trackId: string, muted: boolean)
    onAddTrack()
    onRemoveTrack(trackId: string)
```

```mdl
component ScoreArticle
  desc: |
    Top-level article surface for a Score. Composes TrackList on the left with
    the active Sequence's SequenceGrid on the right.
  props:
    score: Score
  state:
    selectedTrackId?: string
    selectedSequenceId?: string
    playhead?: number        # in beats; null when stopped
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar: tempo, play/stop]      │
    ├──────────┬───────────────────────┤
    │          │                       │
    │ Track    │   SequenceGrid        │
    │ List     │   (selected)          │
    │          │                       │
    └──────────┴───────────────────────┘
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Create Score

  req F-1.1: User can create a new Score from the navtree.
  req F-1.2: New Score has tempo=120, no tracks, no sequences.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Manage Tracks

  req F-2.1:
    when: user adds a track
    then: new Track appended to Score.tracks with a unique id and default name

  req F-2.2:
    when: user removes a track
    then: Track removed AND all Sequences referencing trackId are removed

  req F-2.3:
    when: user mutes a track
    then: Track.muted toggled; playback skips notes from muted tracks
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Edit Sequence Notes

  req F-3.1:
    when: user clicks an empty cell in SequenceGrid
    then: new Note added at (pitch, startTime); duration = beatsPerCell

  req F-3.2:
    when: user clicks a cell containing a note
    then: that Note removed from the Sequence

  req F-3.3:
    when: user drags across empty cells in the same row
    then: Notes are added at each cell along the drag (paint mode)

  req F-3.4:
    when: SequenceGrid is scrolled or zoomed
    then: pitch labels (y-axis) and beat ruler (x-axis) stay frozen / visible
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Playback

  req F-4.1:
    when: user presses play
    then: playhead advances at Score.tempo BPM across the active Sequence

  req F-4.2:
    when: playhead reaches end of Sequence.length
    then: playhead loops to 0 (v1: no score-level transport across sequences)

  req F-4.3:
    when: user presses stop
    then: playhead returns to null; SequenceGrid removes playhead overlay
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Sequence Selection

  req F-5.1:
    when: user clicks a track in TrackList
    then: first Sequence for that track is shown in the SequenceGrid; if no
          Sequence exists for that track, a new empty one is created

  req F-5.2:
    when: selected track changes
    then: SequenceGrid re-renders with the new sequence's notes
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: New Score defaults
  given: a new Score is created
  then:
    - Score.tempo === 120
    - Score.tracks.length === 0
    - Score.sequences.length === 0
```

```mdl
test T-2: Add and remove note
  given: a Score with one track and one (empty) Sequence
  when: user toggles cell (pitch=60, startTime=0)
  then: Sequence.notes.length === 1 AND Sequence.notes[0].pitch === 60
  when: user toggles the same cell again
  then: Sequence.notes.length === 0
```

```mdl
test T-3: Remove track cascades sequences
  given: a Score with a track t1 and 2 sequences referencing t1
  when: user removes track t1
  then: Score.tracks does not contain t1 AND no Sequences reference t1
```

```mdl
test T-4: Playhead loops
  given: a playing Score with active Sequence.length = 4 beats
  when: time advances past 4 beats
  then: playhead position resets to 0 (mod 4)
```
